#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"It's easy to use themes to achieve cross-platform. However, it's easy to "
"spot apps that have been built using themes - they're the ones that don't "
"behave quite like any other app. Widgets don't look *quite* right, or "
"there's a menu bar on a window in an OS X app. Themes can get quite close - "
"but there are always telltale signs."
