#: docs/en/news/posts/2018/buzz/2018-google-summer-of-code-final-report-patience-shyu.md:119
msgid ""
"Minimize boxing of primitive types like String and Int. As VOC is written "
"half in Python, half in Java, a single integer can be found in various "
"representations on its way through the compiler -- as a Python object, "
"unboxed to a primitive Java int, then packaged back up to a Python object. "
"This problem was (somewhat incoherently) addressed in my proposal, but "
"ultimately we couldn't come up with a good abstraction to support it."
msgstr ""

#: docs/en/news/posts/2018/buzz/2018-google-summer-of-code-final-report-patience-shyu.md:126
msgid ""
"Build a peephole optimizer. [CPython's peephole optimizer]{1} scans "
"generated bytecode to identify sequences of bytecode that can be optimized, "
